commit.message:
Change the default timeout to 120s.

That should be a reasonably safe value even if user keeps
the notification alive.
Support generating NEWS off git tags.

Don't delay instantiating Notification.

When implementing actions, it's much easier to fill the data in-place.
Use feature availability macros instead of configure checks.
Bump PV to 1.0.0, to match SONAME.
Adjust --help and --version to be closer to GNU.
Support --foreground option to wait for notification to be closed.

Merge branch 'lib-restored'

In other words, merge libtinynotify-cli & tinynotify-send back together.

Use NotifyCLIFlags to support various additional CLI options.

Note: this breaks API & ABI. Now notification_new_from_cmdline() takes
a NotifyCLIFlags* instead of random arguments, and stores all relevant
information internally there. notify_cli_flags_get_*() functions should
be used to obtain additional information as supported.
Add a quick note on use.
